=== 10.6 The Code: Full microGPT Forward Pass in Python

Configuration is data.
We represent the model's five hyperparameters as a plain list and define selectors once.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=gpt_config]
----

`make_gpt_params` allocates all learnable weights.
`wte` is the token embedding matrix stem:[[|V| \times d\]]; `wpe` is the position embedding matrix.
Weight tying means the unembedding step will reuse `wte` transposed — no separate parameter is stored.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=gpt_params]
----

`gpt_forward` is the full pipeline: embed token IDs, add position embeddings, pass through stem:[N] transformer blocks, apply the final layer norm to the last token's vector, then compute dot products with every row of `wte`.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=gpt_forward]
----

`generate` is the autoregressive loop.

[source,python]
